49extern const CFStringRef kCMFormatDescriptionExtension_SampleDescriptionExtensionAtoms;
50
51static uint8_t convertSubsampling(webrtc::vp9::YuvSubsampling value)
52{
53 switch (value) {
54 case webrtc::vp9::YuvSubsampling::k444:
55 return 3;
56 case webrtc::vp9::YuvSubsampling::k440:
57 return 1;
58 case webrtc::vp9::YuvSubsampling::k422:
59 return 2;
60 case webrtc::vp9::YuvSubsampling::k420:
61 return 1;
62 }
63}
64
65rtc::ScopedCFTypeRef<CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef> computeInputFormat(const uint8_t* data, size_t size, int32_t width, int32_t height)
66{
67 constexpr size_t VPCodecConfigurationContentsSize = 12;
68
69 auto result = webrtc::vp9::ParseIntraFrameInfo(data, size);
70
71 if (!result)
72 return { };
73 auto chromaSubsampling = convertSubsampling(result->sub_sampling);
74 uint8_t bitDepthChromaAndRange = (0xF & (uint8_t)result->bit_detph) << 4 | (0x7 & chromaSubsampling) << 1 | (0x1 & (uint8_t)result->color_range);
75
76 uint8_t record[VPCodecConfigurationContentsSize];
77 memset((void*)record, 0, VPCodecConfigurationContentsSize);
78 // Version and flags (4 bytes)
79 record[0] = 1;
80 // profile
81 record[4] = result->profile;
82 // level
83 record[5] = 10;
84 // bitDepthChromaAndRange
85 record[6] = bitDepthChromaAndRange;
86 // colourPrimaries
87 record[7] = 2; // Unspecified.
88 // transferCharacteristics
89 record[8] = 2; // Unspecified.
90 // matrixCoefficients
91 record[9] = 2; // Unspecified.
92
93 auto cfData = rtc::ScopedCF(CFDataCreate(kCFAllocatorDefault, record, VPCodecConfigurationContentsSize));
94 auto configurationDict = @{ @"vpcC": (__bridge NSData *)cfData.get() };
95 auto extensions = @{ (__bridge NSString *)kCMFormatDescriptionExtension_SampleDescriptionExtensionAtoms: configurationDict };
96
97 CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef formatDescription = nullptr;
98 // Use kCMVideoCodecType_VP9 once added to CMFormatDescription.h
99 if (noErr != CMVideoFormatDescriptionCreate(kCFAllocatorDefault, 'vp09', width, height, (__bridge CFDictionaryRef)extensions, &formatDescription))
100 return { };
101
102 return rtc::ScopedCF(formatDescription);
103}

105// Struct that we pass to the decoder per frame to decode. We receive it again
106// in the decoder callback.
107struct RTCFrameDecodeParams {
108 RTCFrameDecodeParams(RTCVideoDecoderCallback cb, int64_t ts) : callback(cb), timestamp(ts) {}
109 RTCVideoDecoderCallback callback;
110 int64_t timestamp;
111};

113@interface RTCVideoDecoderVTBVP9 ()
114- (void)setError:(OSStatus)error;
115@end
116
117CMSampleBufferRef VP9BufferToCMSampleBuffer(const uint8_t* buffer,
118 size_t buffer_size,
119 CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef video_format) {
120 CMBlockBufferRef new_block_buffer;
121 if (auto error = CMBlockBufferCreateWithMemoryBlock(kCFAllocatorDefault, NULL, buffer_size, kCFAllocatorDefault, NULL, 0, buffer_size, kCMBlockBufferAssureMemoryNowFlag, &new_block_buffer)) {
122 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "VP9BufferToCMSampleBuffer CMBlockBufferCreateWithMemoryBlock failed with: " << error;
123 return nullptr;
124 }
125 auto block_buffer = rtc::ScopedCF(new_block_buffer);
126
127 if (auto error = CMBlockBufferReplaceDataBytes(buffer, block_buffer.get(), 0, buffer_size)) {
128 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "VP9BufferToCMSampleBuffer CMBlockBufferReplaceDataBytes failed with: " << error;
129 return nullptr;
130 }
131
132 CMSampleBufferRef sample_buffer = nullptr;
133 if (auto error = CMSampleBufferCreate(kCFAllocatorDefault, block_buffer.get(), true, nullptr, nullptr, video_format, 1, 0, nullptr, 0, nullptr, &sample_buffer)) {
134 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "VP9BufferToCMSampleBuffer CMSampleBufferCreate failed with: " << error;
135 return nullptr;
136 }
137 return sample_buffer;
138}
139
140// This is the callback function that VideoToolbox calls when decode is
141// complete.
142void vp9DecompressionOutputCallback(void *decoderRef,
143 void *params,
144 OSStatus status,
145 VTDecodeInfoFlags infoFlags,
146 CVImageBufferRef imageBuffer,
147 CMTime timestamp,
148 CMTime duration) {
149 if (status != noErr || !imageBuffer) {
150 RTCVideoDecoderVTBVP9 *decoder = (__bridge RTCVideoDecoderVTBVP9 *)decoderRef;
151 [decoder setError:status != noErr ? status : 1];
152 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to decode frame. Status: " << status;
153 return;
154 }
155
156 std::unique_ptr<RTCFrameDecodeParams> decodeParams(reinterpret_cast<RTCFrameDecodeParams *>(params));
157 RTCCVPixelBuffer *frameBuffer = [[RTCCVPixelBuffer alloc] initWithPixelBuffer:imageBuffer];
158 RTCVideoFrame *decodedFrame =
159 [[RTCVideoFrame alloc] initWithBuffer:frameBuffer
160 rotation:RTCVideoRotation_0
161 timeStampNs:CMTimeGetSeconds(timestamp) * rtc::kNumNanosecsPerSec];
162 decodedFrame.timeStamp = decodeParams->timestamp;
163 decodeParams->callback(decodedFrame);
164}

166// Decoder.
167@implementation RTCVideoDecoderVTBVP9 {
168 CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef _videoFormat;
169 VTDecompressionSessionRef _decompressionSession;
170 RTCVideoDecoderCallback _callback;
171 OSStatus _error;
172 int32_t _width;
173 int32_t _height;
174 bool _shouldCheckFormat;
175}
176
177- (instancetype)init {
178 self = [super init];
179 if (self) {
180 _shouldCheckFormat = true;
181 }
182 return self;
183}
184
185- (void)dealloc {
186 [self destroyDecompressionSession];
187 [self setVideoFormat:nullptr];
188}
189
190- (NSInteger)startDecodeWithNumberOfCores:(int)numberOfCores {
191 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
192}
193
194- (NSInteger)decode:(RTCEncodedImage *)inputImage
195 missingFrames:(BOOL)missingFrames
196 codecSpecificInfo:(nullable id<RTCCodecSpecificInfo>)info
197 renderTimeMs:(int64_t)renderTimeMs {
198 RTC_DCHECK(inputImage.buffer);
199 if (inputImage.frameType == RTCFrameTypeVideoFrameKey) {
200 [self setWidth:inputImage.encodedWidth height: inputImage.encodedHeight];
201 }
202 return [self decodeData: (uint8_t *)inputImage.buffer.bytes size: inputImage.buffer.length timeStamp: inputImage.timeStamp];
203}
204
205- (void)setWidth:(uint16_t)width height:(uint16_t)height {
206 _width = width;
207 _height = height;
208 _shouldCheckFormat = true;
209}
210
211- (NSInteger)decodeData:(const uint8_t *)data
212 size:(size_t)size
213 timeStamp:(uint32_t)timeStamp {
214
215 if (_error != noErr) {
216 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Last frame decode failed.";
217 _error = noErr;
218 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
219 }
220
221 if (_shouldCheckFormat || !_videoFormat) {
222 auto inputFormat = computeInputFormat(data, size, _width, _height);
223 if (inputFormat) {
224 _shouldCheckFormat = false;
225 // Check if the video format has changed, and reinitialize decoder if
226 // needed.
227 if (!CMFormatDescriptionEqual(inputFormat.get(), _videoFormat)) {
228 [self setVideoFormat:inputFormat.get()];
229 int resetDecompressionSessionError = [self resetDecompressionSession];
230 if (resetDecompressionSessionError != WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK) {
231 [self setVideoFormat:nullptr];
232 return resetDecompressionSessionError;
233 }
234 }
235 }
236 }
237 if (!_videoFormat) {
238 // We received a frame but we don't have format information so we can't
239 // decode it.
240 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Missing video format.";
241 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
242 }
243 auto sampleBuffer = rtc::ScopedCF(VP9BufferToCMSampleBuffer(data, size, _videoFormat));
244 if (!sampleBuffer) {
245 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
246 }
247
248 VTDecodeFrameFlags decodeFlags = kVTDecodeFrame_EnableAsynchronousDecompression;
249 std::unique_ptr<RTCFrameDecodeParams> frameDecodeParams;
250 frameDecodeParams.reset(new RTCFrameDecodeParams(_callback, timeStamp));
251 OSStatus status = VTDecompressionSessionDecodeFrame(
252 _decompressionSession, sampleBuffer.get(), decodeFlags, frameDecodeParams.release(), nullptr);
253#if defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
254 // Re-initialize the decoder if we have an invalid session while the app is
255 // active or decoder malfunctions and retry the decode request.
256 if ((status == kVTInvalidSessionErr || status == kVTVideoDecoderMalfunctionErr) &&
257 [self resetDecompressionSession] == WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK) {
258 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Failed to decode frame with code: " << status
259 << " retrying decode after decompression session reset";
260 frameDecodeParams.reset(new RTCFrameDecodeParams(_callback, timeStamp));
261 status = VTDecompressionSessionDecodeFrame(
262 _decompressionSession, sampleBuffer.get(), decodeFlags, frameDecodeParams.release(), nullptr);
263 }
264#endif
265 if (status != noErr) {
266 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to decode frame with code: " << status;
267 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
268 }
269 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
270}
271
272- (void)setCallback:(RTCVideoDecoderCallback)callback {
273 _callback = callback;
274}
275
276- (void)setError:(OSStatus)error {
277 _error = error;
278}
279
280- (NSInteger)releaseDecoder {
281 // Need to invalidate the session so that callbacks no longer occur and it
282 // is safe to null out the callback.
283 [self destroyDecompressionSession];
284 [self setVideoFormat:nullptr];
285 _callback = nullptr;
286 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
287}
288
289#pragma mark - Private
290
291- (int)resetDecompressionSession {
292 [self destroyDecompressionSession];
293
294 if (!_videoFormat) {
295 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
296 }
297
298 // Set keys for OpenGL and IOSurface compatibilty, which makes the encoder
299 // create pixel buffers with GPU backed memory. The intent here is to pass
300 // the pixel buffers directly so we avoid a texture upload later during
301 // rendering. This currently is moot because we are converting back to an
302 // I420 frame after decode, but eventually we will be able to plumb
303 // CVPixelBuffers directly to the renderer.
304 // TODO(tkchin): Maybe only set OpenGL/IOSurface keys if we know that that
305 // we can pass CVPixelBuffers as native handles in decoder output.
306 static size_t const attributesSize = 3;
307 CFTypeRef keys[attributesSize] = {
308#if defined(WEBRTC_MAC) || defined(WEBRTC_MAC_CATALYST)
309 kCVPixelBufferOpenGLCompatibilityKey,
310#elif defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
311 kCVPixelBufferOpenGLESCompatibilityKey,
312#endif
313 kCVPixelBufferIOSurfacePropertiesKey,
314 kCVPixelBufferPixelFormatTypeKey
315 };
316 CFDictionaryRef ioSurfaceValue = CreateCFTypeDictionary(nullptr, nullptr, 0);
317 int64_t nv12type = kCVPixelFormatType_420YpCbCr8BiPlanarFullRange;
318 CFNumberRef pixelFormat = CFNumberCreate(nullptr, kCFNumberLongType, &nv12type);
319 CFTypeRef values[attributesSize] = {kCFBooleanTrue, ioSurfaceValue, pixelFormat};
320 CFDictionaryRef attributes = CreateCFTypeDictionary(keys, values, attributesSize);
321 if (ioSurfaceValue) {
322 CFRelease(ioSurfaceValue);
323 ioSurfaceValue = nullptr;
324 }
325 if (pixelFormat) {
326 CFRelease(pixelFormat);
327 pixelFormat = nullptr;
328 }
329
330 VTDecompressionOutputCallbackRecord record = {
331 vp9DecompressionOutputCallback, (__bridge void *)self,
332 };
333 OSStatus status = VTDecompressionSessionCreate(
334 nullptr, _videoFormat, nullptr, attributes, &record, &_decompressionSession);
335 CFRelease(attributes);
336 if (status != noErr) {
337 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create decompression session: " << status;
338 [self destroyDecompressionSession];
339 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
340 }
341 [self configureDecompressionSession];
342
343 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
344}
345
346- (void)configureDecompressionSession {
347 RTC_DCHECK(_decompressionSession);
348#if defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
349 VTSessionSetProperty(_decompressionSession, kVTDecompressionPropertyKey_RealTime, kCFBooleanTrue);
350#endif
351}
352
353- (void)destroyDecompressionSession {
354 if (_decompressionSession) {
355#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
356 VTDecompressionSessionWaitForAsynchronousFrames(_decompressionSession);
357#else
358#if defined(WEBRTC_IOS)
359 if ([UIDevice isIOS11OrLater]) {
360 VTDecompressionSessionWaitForAsynchronousFrames(_decompressionSession);
361 }
362#endif
363#endif
364 VTDecompressionSessionInvalidate(_decompressionSession);
365 CFRelease(_decompressionSession);
366 _decompressionSession = nullptr;
367 }
368}
369
370- (void)setVideoFormat:(CMVideoFormatDescriptionRef)videoFormat {
371 if (_videoFormat == videoFormat) {
372 return;
373 }
374 if (_videoFormat) {
375 CFRelease(_videoFormat);
376 }
377 _videoFormat = videoFormat;
378 if (_videoFormat) {
379 CFRetain(_videoFormat);
380 }
381}

383- (NSString *)implementationName {
384 return @"VideoToolbox";
385}
